         "title": "Nuno Bettencourt: “Everyone sucks at guitar for a long time. When people say I am blessed I say no, it was the 10,000 hours of practice”",
         "description": "<p><span>Nuno Bettencourt, one of the most celebrated guitarists in rock, left the Azores for Massachusetts at four years. The Extreme founder sits with Tony Gonçalves to revisit a journey that took him from his brother’s verdict “you’ll never amount to anything in music” to global stages, a Grammy, and the obsession with craft that still keeps him writing songs in hotel rooms while the tour bus rolls on</span></p>",
